{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_59","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/daemon_issue_intake.feature | sed -n '1,120p'\"","aggregated_output":"     1\tFeature: Daemon Issue Watchers and Requirements Handoff\n     2\t  The daemon polls external issue sources, creates tasks through routing rules,\n     3\t  and dispatches into workflow execution or requirements handoff paths.\n     4\t\n     5\t  # DAEMON-INTAKE-001\n     6\t  Scenario: DAEMON-INTAKE-001 - Watcher ingestion creates task from watched issue\n     7\t    Given a workspace is initialized\n     8\t    And a watched issue file exists with issue_ref \"test/repo#1\" and source_revision \"abc12345\"\n     9\t    When the daemon polls for new issues\n    10\t    Then a pending task is created for issue_ref \"test/repo#1\"\n    11\t    And the task has source_revision \"abc12345\"\n    12\t    And the task dispatch_mode is \"workflow\"\n    13\t\n    14\t  # DAEMON-INTAKE-002\n    15\t  Scenario: DAEMON-INTAKE-002 - Idempotent re-polling skips existing issue\n    16\t    Given a workspace is initialized\n    17\t    And a task already exists for issue_ref \"test/repo#1\" with source_revision \"abc12345\"\n    18\t    When the watcher returns the same issue_ref and source_revision\n    19\t    Then no new task is created\n    20\t    And the existing task remains unchanged\n    21\t\n    22\t  # DAEMON-INTAKE-003\n    23\t  Scenario: DAEMON-INTAKE-003 - Requirements quick handoff completes in one cycle\n    24\t    Given a workspace is initialized\n    25\t    And a watched issue with \"/rb requirements quick\" command\n    26\t    When the daemon processes the task\n    27\t    Then the requirements run completes with a seed\n    28\t    And the task is linked to the requirements_run_id\n    29\t    And the task transitions to completed\n    30\t\n    31\t  # DAEMON-INTAKE-004\n    32\t  Scenario: DAEMON-INTAKE-004 - Requirements draft enters waiting state\n    33\t    Given a workspace is initialized\n    34\t    And a watched issue with \"/rb requirements draft\" command\n    35\t    When the daemon processes the task\n    36\t    Then the requirements run creates a question set\n    37\t    And the task transitions to waiting_for_requirements\n    38\t    And the task holds no lease, no writer lock, and no active workflow run\n    39\t\n    40\t  # DAEMON-INTAKE-005\n    41\t  Scenario: DAEMON-INTAKE-005 - Duplicate issue with different revision rejected\n    42\t    Given a workspace is initialized\n    43\t    And a non-terminal task exists for issue_ref \"test/repo#2\"\n    44\t    When the watcher returns issue_ref \"test/repo#2\" with a different source_revision\n    45\t    Then the ingestion fails with DuplicateWatchedIssue\n    46\t    And no new task is created\n    47\t\n    48\t  # DAEMON-INTAKE-006\n    49\t  Scenario: DAEMON-INTAKE-006 - Routed flow overrides seed recommendation\n    50\t    Given a workspace is initialized\n    51\t    And a watched issue with routing command \"/rb flow quick_dev\"\n    52\t    And the completed seed recommends flow \"standard\"\n    53\t    When the daemon creates the project from the seed\n    54\t    Then the project uses flow \"quick_dev\" (the routed flow)\n    55\t    And a warning is recorded about the flow override\n    56\t\n    57\t  # DAEMON-INTAKE-007\n    58\t  Scenario: DAEMON-INTAKE-007 - Unknown requirements command fails ingestion\n    59\t    Given a workspace is initialized\n    60\t    And a watched issue body contains \"/rb requirements unknown\"\n    61\t    When the watcher attempts to ingest the issue\n    62\t    Then ingestion fails with WatcherIngestionFailed\n    63\t    And no task is created\n    64\t\n    65\t  # DAEMON-INTAKE-008\n    66\t  Scenario: DAEMON-INTAKE-008 - Daemon status surfaces waiting state\n    67\t    Given a workspace is initialized\n    68\t    And a task exists in waiting_for_requirements with requirements_run_id \"req-123\"\n    69\t    When \"daemon status\" is run\n    70\t    Then the output includes \"waiting_for_requirements\"\n    71\t    And the output includes \"requirements_run=req-123\"\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
